            <item>
                <title>got atom-shell 404 issue when updating atom</title>
                <pubDate>Thu, 31 Mar 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
                <link>https://blog.dotone.top/blog/it/got-atom-shell-404-issue-when-updating-atom/</link>
                <guid>https://blog.dotone.top/blog/it/got-atom-shell-404-issue-when-updating-atom/</guid>
                <description>&lt;p&gt;Recent days I tried several times to update Atom packages from both Atom and apm update command, but failed finally.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So I decided to look what happened by running command:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre style=&quot;background-color:#212121;&quot;&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;color:#82aaff;&quot;&gt;apm update&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#89ddff;&quot;&gt; --&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#f78c6c;&quot;&gt;verbose
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It seems it failed to download atom-shell.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Googled with &#x27;atom-shell 404&#x27; and found this link https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;atom&#x2F;atom&#x2F;issues&#x2F;11080.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The solution mentioned did the trick.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
